{% comment %}
  Preorder status check — documentation snippet

  Pre-order is activated solely by the custom.preorder_ship_date metafield (type: date).
  If a future date is set → product is pre-order.
  If no date, or date has passed → product is normal / in-stock.

  No tags required. No theme.preorder metafield required.

  CANONICAL PREORDER CHECK LOGIC (copy this block wherever needed):

    assign is_preorder = false
    if settings.preorder_enable
      assign preorder_ship_date_val = product.metafields.custom.preorder_ship_date.value
      if preorder_ship_date_val != blank
        assign preorder_date_int = preorder_ship_date_val | date: '%Y%m%d' | plus: 0
        assign today_int = 'now' | date: '%Y%m%d' | plus: 0
        if today_int < preorder_date_int
          assign is_preorder = true
        endif
      endif
    endif

  For cart line items, replace `product` with `line_item.product`.
  Add `and current_variant.available` to the outer if when on product pages.
{% endcomment %}
